Dialogue: 0,1:30:27.27,1:30:28.95,Default,,0,0,0,,可是我太懦弱{\fs14}\NBut I was weak.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:29.78,1:30:34.54,Default,,0,0,0,,我不認為自己帶著女兒能有一份像樣的人生{\fs14}\NI didn't think I can live and surpport myself and my daughter.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:35.19,1:30:39.37,Default,,0,0,0,,而且他說要不是靠他的個人魅力 我的畫會無人問津{\fs14}\NAnd he said nobody would buy the paintings without his personality.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:41.76,1:30:43.49,Default,,0,0,0,,也許他有對的地方{\fs14}\NMaybe he was right.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:45.94,1:30:49.34,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,你很會引人注目 {\fs14}\NYou were very talented been charming,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:49.34,1:30:53.61,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,也是銷售和推廣的天才{\fs14}\Nand you're a genius at sale and promotion.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:56.33,1:31:00.05,Default,,0,0,0,,聽上去你好像描述得是兩個人啊{\fs14}\NIt sounds like you're describing two different man.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:01.12,1:31:06.78,Default,,0,0,0,,一個是可怕的魔鬼 另一個卻是討喜的上流紳士{\fs14}\NOne a sadistic ogre, the other one a delightful bon vivant.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:07.56,1:31:10.76,Default,,0,0,0,,那正是你 沃爾特 你就像化身博士{\fs14}\NThat's you, Walter, you're Jekyll and Hyde.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:07.56,1:31:10.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(202.2,34.116)}化身博士有人格分裂
Dialogue: 0,1:31:11.51,1:31:12.80,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,那是惡語中傷 {\fs14}\NThat's outrageous statement!
Dialogue: 0,1:31:12.80,1:31:14.84,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我要求法庭記錄將其刪去{\fs14}\NI demand we strike it out from the record.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:15.09,1:31:16.06,Default,,0,0,0,,駁回{\fs14}\NOverrule!
Dialogue: 0,1:31:16.91,1:31:21.12,Default,,0,0,0,,你才是惡語中傷 總是指責我 讓我疲於應對{\fs14}\NYou were outrageous, constantly criticise me, wore me down ...
Dialogue: 0,1:31:21.30,1:31:24.37,Default,,0,0,0,,威脅我說如果我說出真相就殺了我{\fs14}\N... saying you would have me knocked off if I told the truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:24.68,1:31:26.20,Default,,0,0,0,,可我現在說的就是真相{\fs14}\NWell, I'm telling the truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:26.43,1:31:27.74,Default,,0,0,0,,法官大人{\fs14}\NYour Honor!
Dialogue: 0,1:31:28.03,1:31:29.43,Default,,0,0,0,,請求未決審判{\fs14}\NI asks for mistrial.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:29.46,1:31:32.58,Default,,0,0,0,,你是個騙子 你的字典裡根本就沒有真話二字{\fs14}\NYou're a liar, you don't even know what the truth is!
Dialogue: 0,1:31:32.87,1:31:35.26,Default,,0,0,0,,你根本就沒有 而我現在能說出真相{\fs14}\NYou don't even know, but I'm stating the truth now.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:35.46,1:31:37.06,Default,,0,0,0,,你沒法讓我噤聲{\fs14}\NYou can not shut me up!
Dialogue: 0,1:31:38.97,1:31:42.14,Default,,0,0,0,,這不是一場家庭口角 或許說晚了點{\fs14}\NThis is not a domestic squabble, or maybe it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:42.86,1:31:45.65,Default,,0,0,0,,不過我們剩下的人可沒興趣看你倆吵下去{\fs14}\NBut the rest of us have no interest in watching you two go at it.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:50.03,1:31:52.33,Default,,0,0,0,,我很抱歉失態了{\fs14}\NI'm sorry for my emotion.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:54.42,1:31:56.11,Default,,0,0,0,,我是位藝術家{\fs14}\NI'm a artist.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:57.80,1:31:59.23,Default,,0,0,0,,也許吧{\fs14}\NMaybe.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:00.47,1:32:01.74,Default,,0,0,0,,法官大人{\fs14}\NYour Honor!
Dialogue: 0,1:32:02.22,1:32:07.27,Default,,0,0,0,,我現在請出我的證人 沃爾特·斯坦利·基恩先生{\fs14}\NI call as my witness, Mr. Walter Stanley Keane!
Dialogue: 0,1:32:14.12,1:32:15.78,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,你發誓所說一切屬實 {\fs14}\NYou swear to tell the truth, the whole truth,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:15.78,1:32:18.44,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,絕無半點隱瞞和謊言 願上帝保佑你{\fs14}\N nothing but the truth, so help you God?
Dialogue: 0,1:32:18.67,1:32:20.04,Default,,0,0,0,,是的{\fs14}\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:27.79,1:32:32.69,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,基恩先生 似乎對於「大眼睛孤兒」的起源{\fs14}\NMr. Keane, there seems a lot of in your window
Dialogue: 0,1:32:32.69,1:32:36.56,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,有很多風言風語和矛盾百出的證詞{\fs14}\Nand contradictory testimony about the genesis of the "Big Eye Waifs"
Dialogue: 0,1:32:37.21,1:32:42.95,Default,,0,0,0,,你能不能向法庭澄清是誰創作了這些畫{\fs14}\NWould you mind clarify to this court who spawn these paintings?
Dialogue: 0,1:32:48.30,1:32:51.12,Default,,0,0,0,,為什麼 是我創作的這些孤兒畫{\fs14}\NWhy, I created these children.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:55.39,1:32:58.15,Default,,0,0,0,,法庭不是你表演的舞台 坐好了說{\fs14}\NChoreography is not necessary, Just sit down and testify.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:07.02,1:33:08.96,Default,,0,0,0,,我的人生豐富多彩{\fs14}\NI had a wonderful life.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:09.86,1:33:14.85,Default,,0,0,0,,作為一名藝術家 數不清的名人爭著做我朋友{\fs14}\NI was a artist, and friend of untold celebrities.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:14.96,1:33:17.75,Default,,0,0,0,,然而 當我驀然回首這一生{\fs14}\NYeah, when I look back at all ...
Dialogue: 0,1:33:17.83,1:33:20.98,Default,,0,0,0,,發現做過最重要的事{\fs14}\N... to define what really mattered ...
Dialogue: 0,1:33:21.28,1:33:26.08,Default,,0,0,0,,就是為世界上的孤兒盡了些微薄之力{\fs14}\N... it was that I was dedicated to hungry children of the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:28.58,1:33:33.49,Default,,0,0,0,,一切始於柏林 二戰後{\fs14}\NIt all began in Berlin, after World War II ...
Dialogue: 0,1:33:34.17,1:33:41.72,Default,,0,0,0,,那些滿是傷痕的孤兒緊緊抓住鐵網{\fs14}\NThe orphans clutching part of wire, their bodies lacerated ...
Dialogue: 0,1:33:42.95,1:33:46.67,Default,,0,0,0,,小手如同乾柴 大大的眼睛{\fs14}\N... their fingers scrawny ... their eyes big.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:49.14,1:33:51.17,Default,,0,0,0,,瓊·克勞福德女士走出{\fs14}\NMrs. Joan Crawford walked out ...
Dialogue: 0,1:33:51.30,1:33:53.72,Default,,0,0,0,,基恩先生 請坐好{\fs14}\NMr. Keane, sit down.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:54.35,1:33:55.64,Default,,0,0,0,,瑪麗蓮·夢露{\fs14}\NMarilyn Monroe ...
Dialogue: 0,1:33:55.84,1:33:57.44,Default,,0,0,0,,我和牛頓{\fs14}\Nthe Newton and I ...
Dialogue: 0,1:33:58.04,1:34:00.90,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,傑裡·劉易斯打電話請我畫他們全家{\fs14}\NJerry Lewis calls me says I wants you to paint me
Dialogue: 0,1:34:00.90,1:34:02.34,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,身著小丑服的樣子{\fs14}\Nand my family in clown suits.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:02.71,1:34:06.74,Default,,0,0,0,,娜塔莉·伍德女士走過來對我說{\fs14}\NMrs. Natalie Wood walked out to me and said ...
Dialogue: 0,1:34:07.54,1:34:13.53,Default,,0,0,0,,"這是我一生當中見過畫的最美的一幅畫！"{\fs14}\N"This is the greatest single painting I've ever seen in my entire life!"
Dialogue: 0,1:34:13.64,1:34:14.62,Default,,0,0,0,,你不用說了{\fs14}\NYou done!
Dialogue: 0,1:34:14.91,1:34:16.76,Default,,0,0,0,,- 我還沒說完呢 - 這我說了算{\fs14}\N- I'm not finished. - Actually you are!
Dialogue: 0,1:34:17.14,1:34:19.99,Default,,0,0,0,,我實在是受不了你那些故作煽情 冗長無趣的故事了{\fs14}\NI can not stand one more wire or shaggy dog tale.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:20.29,1:34:22.09,Default,,0,0,0,,你根本不是在作證 完全是在搗亂{\fs14}\NYou're not testify, you filibuster it.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:22.21,1:34:26.03,Default,,0,0,0,,不需要你的那些廢話 聯邦法庭就已經不堪重負了{\fs14}\NFederal court overburden enough without you ducky clacking nonsense.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:26.45,1:34:29.12,Default,,0,0,0,,我們可以在這耗到死{\fs14}\NWe can stay here until we grow old and die ...
Dialogue: 0,1:34:29.35,1:34:31.93,Default,,0,0,0,,不過這個案子很明顯就是你和{\fs14}\N... but it's obvious this case boils down to your words ...
Dialogue: 0,1:34:32.04,1:34:33.53,Default,,0,0,0,,基恩女士各執一詞{\fs14}\N... versus Mrs. Keane's words.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:33.73,1:34:34.33,Default,,0,0,0,,未決審判{\fs14}\NMistrial.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:34.56,1:34:36.43,Default,,0,0,0,,不 這不會是未決審判{\fs14}\NNo, it's not a mistrial!
Dialogue: 0,1:34:37.75,1:34:41.54,Default,,0,0,0,,以我的觀點 只有一個辦法可以找出真相{\fs14}\NIn my opinion, there is only one way to clear this thing up.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:43.65,1:34:45.76,Default,,0,0,0,,你們倆都作一幅畫{\fs14}\NYou're both going to paint!
Dialogue: 0,1:34:48.55,1:34:50.39,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,好了 把畫架搬過來 {\fs14}\NAll right, bring those easels down,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:50.39,1:34:51.87,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,擺在兩邊的椅子旁{\fs14}\Nset them up on both side of the bench.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:05.03,1:35:07.11,Default,,0,0,0,,先說下我不需要什麼大作{\fs14}\NNow I'm not looking for a master piece.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:07.31,1:35:08.72,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我對這些瞭解不多 {\fs14}\NI'm don't know much about these things,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:08.72,1:35:10.61,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,業餘水準 也當不了評論家{\fs14}\N I'm a amateur, not art critic.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:10.89,1:35:12.92,Default,,0,0,0,,不過1個小時夠了吧{\fs14}\NBut is one hour enough?
Dialogue: 0,1:35:13.71,1:35:15.13,Default,,0,0,0,,恩 法官大人{\fs14}\NYes, Your Honor.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:18.36,1:35:19.31,Default,,0,0,0,,那麼好{\fs14}\NOk, then.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:19.79,1:35:22.87,Default,,0,0,0,,給你們倆都提供了相同的器具{\fs14}\NYou both been provided with identical supplies.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:23.12,1:35:26.15,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,那麼 沒有其他事的話 基恩女士 基恩先生{\fs14}\NSo, without any further business, Mrs. Keane, Mr. Keane.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:26.15,1:35:27.37,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,法庭交給你們了{\fs14}\Nthe court is yours.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:34.80,1:36:36.38,Default,,0,0,0,,基恩先生{\fs14}\NMr. Keane?
Dialogue: 0,1:36:38.89,1:36:40.90,Default,,0,0,0,,只是平心靜氣{\fs14}\NJust setting them.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:43.16,1:36:45.21,Default,,0,0,0,,等候靈感出現{\fs14}\NWaiting for the muse to strike.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:46.48,1:36:49.40,Default,,0,0,0,,那好吧 你的靈感還有58分鐘{\fs14}\NWell, your muse has 58 minutes.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:19.06,1:37:21.02,Default,,0,0,0,,基恩先生 你沒事吧{\fs14}\NMr. Keane, are you alright?
Dialogue: 0,1:37:24.14,1:37:29.67,Default,,0,0,0,,我肩膀的舊傷又犯了 肌肉拉傷{\fs14}\NMy old shoulder injury just flare up a bad muscle.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:31.37,1:37:33.99,Default,,0,0,0,,我一直有吃消炎藥{\fs14}\NI've been taking medicationg for inflammation ...
Dialogue: 0,1:37:50.53,1:37:52.60,Default,,0,0,0,,我想今天是沒法動筆了{\fs14}\NI don't think I will be able to paint today.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:10.90,1:38:13.74,Default,,0,0,0,,陪審團裁定瑪格麗特·基恩的各項控訴成立{\fs14}\NThe jury found a favour with Margaret Keane on all points.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:13.84,1:38:15.89,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,她要繼續提出誹謗 {\fs14}\NShe went on charges of defamation,
Dialogue: 0,1:38:15.89,1:38:18.63,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,情感傷害 名譽侵害等指控{\fs14}\N emotional destress, and damaged reputation.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:19.23,1:38:21.23,Default,,0,0,0,,祝賀你  瑪格麗特{\fs14}\NCongratulation... Margaret ...
Dialogue: 0,1:38:21.53,1:38:23.13,Default,,0,0,0,,謝謝大家 非常感謝{\fs14}\NThank you, thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:24.35,1:38:26.48,Default,,0,0,0,,瑪格麗特 你要給這幅畫起個什麼名字{\fs14}\NMargaret, what do you going to call the painting?
Dialogue: 0,1:38:27.99,1:38:30.42,Default,,0,0,0,,非賣品224號{\fs14}\Nexhibit 224.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:27.99,1:38:30.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(194.4,26.624)}提摩太后書2章2至4節：你在許多見證人面前聽見我所教訓的
Dialogue: 0,1:38:27.99,1:38:30.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(241.8,54.092)}也要交託那忠心能教導別人的人
Dialogue: 0,1:38:32.74,1:38:35.00,Default,,0,0,0,,瑪格麗特 能給我簽個名嗎{\fs14}\NMargaret, can I possibly have your autograph?
Dialogue: 0,1:38:36.88,1:38:38.55,Default,,0,0,0,,兩件事對瑪格麗特最為重要{\fs14}\NTwo things matter to Margaret. </ I>
Dialogue: 0,1:38:38.75,1:38:40.45,Default,,0,0,0,,她的畫和女兒{\fs14}\NHer daughter and her paintings. </ I>
Dialogue: 0,1:38:40.93,1:38:43.35,Default,,0,0,0,,在經歷了各種風風雨雨後{\fs14}\NAnd after all the crazy turn the story took ... </ i>
Dialogue: 0,1:38:43.69,1:38:46.19,Default,,0,0,0,,她終於見到彩虹 {\fs14}\N... she came out the end with bountiful. </ I>
